							⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️ input styling : ⭐️ ⭐️ ⭐️

👉️ border: none -> to remove the shadow thingy.
👉️ padding-left: px -> to move the caret.
👉️ caret: unset; -> to not display the caret. but it gets displayed on active.
	caret-color: #color; -> sets the color of the caret.
	background-color: #color; -> sets the background of the input

👉️ pesudo-elements w.r.t inputs :

Pseudo-elements like ::before and ::after are typically used with container elements that have content. 
However, input elements are self-closing and cannot have child elements.
If you want to add additional elements or visuals to the input field, you can wrap the input element inside 
a container element and apply the pseudo-element styles to the containe

👉️ styling placeholder:
 use :- placeholder selector.
 i.e :- &::placeholder { 
 		 // css..
 		}

👉️ Removing the default "clear-icon":

	&::-webkit-search-cancel-button {
 			display: none;
		}
